snippet.textDisplay: AC family! I recently saw a animated TED talk about solenopsis geminata AKA Fire Ants that described something I hadn't known and wondered if anyone had witnessed this behavior. During the early stages of a fresh Fire Ant colony they describe the queen laying 2 types of eggs. Fertilized and Unfertilized eggs. They go on to say that the queen and Nanitics will eat these eggs for early nourishment. Here in these videos you describe it quite differently as a nutritious soup made in the queens body and shared with the Nanitics until they are strong enough to forage for food. I had assumed that it was like breast milk that was created and stayed in her body until fed to the larva through trophallaxis, not expelled as a useless/non larva forming egg and re consumed. From everything I have learned here at the AC family I dont believe this is true and want another opinion on the matter.
snippet.textOriginal: AC family! I recently saw a animated TED talk about solenopsis geminata AKA Fire Ants that described something I hadn't known and wondered if anyone had witnessed this behavior. During the early stages of a fresh Fire Ant colony they describe the queen laying 2 types of eggs. Fertilized and Unfertilized eggs. They go on to say that the queen and Nanitics will eat these eggs for early nourishment.
